Xenith is InferNode's text environment. It is a fork of Inferno's Acme editor
(appl/acme/): roughly two dozen source files share direct lineage with Acme
(buff.b, col.b, dat.b, disk.b, ecmd.b, edit.b, elog.b, exec.b, file.b,
frame.b, fsys.b, graph.b, gui.b, look.b, regx.b, row.b, scrl.b, styxaux.b,
text.b, time.b, util.b, wind.b, xfid.b), alongside InferNode-specific work.

Acme was authored at Bell Laboratories and ported to Inferno/Limbo by Vita
Nuova. Vita Nuova relicensed all of Inferno — Acme included — under the
permissive MIT licence. Xenith and its Acme-derived files are therefore made
available under MIT. No part of Xenith is or was licensed under the GPL.

